ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A seminar-style class that reads interesting cell bio papers every week and discusses them. Would recommend for those interested in cell biology or those wishing to learn more about cell bio in a low-pressure setting.

In this class, students will read a different research article each week. One student will present some background information while the other students go around the room sequentially describing each figure in detail. I would recommend this class if you enjoy seminars instead of lectures.

Very comparable to Methods and Logic for MBB. You read papers, write a summary, and discuss. I would recommend this class to anyone not comfortable in reading scientific articles, as it definitely improved my skill level.
This is a very nice course to read papers every week and discuss. I've learned a lot this semester!
I would highly recommend this course to an person interested in learning about cellular biology or entering the department

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Helped me in reading scientific journals.
I was able to know more on the different techniques being used, the different cellular mechanisms and also the hottest topics of research in the field.
This course provided background information for my thesis project and set the tone for me to chose which lab to join.
